column17:
The posts that use a distract tactic are:

@knj_brasil @secawards I vote #RM for #ArtistaAsiatico at the 2023 #SECAwards Marcos

This post adds the irrelevant detail of "2023" to the original topic of voting for RM for ArtistaAsiatico at the SECAwards. By adding this irrelevant information, it distracts from the main focus of the tweet, which is the voting. This is a common tactic used in coordinated campaigns to confuse or mislead the audience.
